      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Standard modeling procedures were followed per internal SOP. Peer review of model setup was conducted by a second analyst."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form adequacy requires that the constitutive model, contact formulation, and boundary conditions are justified by literature or prior validation studies. Gradation 3 requires documented justification for each major modeling assumption with supporting references.",
      "rationale": "Linear-elastic isotropic material model is justified for titanium alloy at sub-yield loading. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and rod is based on published tribological data for Ti-6Al-4V interfaces. Boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as confirmed by coordinate measurements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to specimen-specific measurements or certified material test reports. Gradation 3 requires uncertainty quantification on key inputs with propagation to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) for Ti-6Al-4V ELI are taken from material certificates for the specific lot. Geometric dimensions are from coordinate measuring machine (CMM) reports for each of the 11 constructs. Input uncertainty was propagated using Monte Carlo sampling."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples must be representative of the production device. Gradation 3 requires traceability of samples to production lots with documented dimensional inspection.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-lot components. Each construct was dimensionally inspected by CMM prior to testing. Sample traceability records are archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 compression-bending at 5 degrees). Only one test condition was evaluated, which limits the ability to characterize model behavior across the full operating envelope. This factor is below the required level; the shortfall is noted and accepted given that the single condition is the clinically dominant loading mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "Model inputs were matched to experimental specimen measurements on a construct-by-construct basis. Equivalency was confirmed for geometry and material properties."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative output comparison must use a normalized validation metric. Gradation 3 requires E/uval metric (ratio of model error to combined experimental and simulation uncertainty) with a threshold of 1.96 at 95% confidence, and percent difference below 10% for each QoI.",
      "rationale": "E/uval was computed for stiffness (0.84), yield force (1.12), and force at 40 mm (0.97), all below the 1.96 threshold. Percent differences were 4.2%, 6.8%, and 5.1% respectively, all within the 10% acceptance bound."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "The QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly specified by ASTM F1717 and are clinically relevant indicators of construct integrity under compression-bending."
